AGI - A 16-year-old was rescued in the evening after being stabbed - just before 21, in via Pier Paolo Pasolini - outside the Merlata Bloom shopping center, on the northwest outskirts of Milan.
The young man was transported in red code to the Niguarda hospital. &nbsp;&nbsp; The attack would have matured during a robbery attempt by a group of other young people.
After having encircled the young man, now admitted and out of danger of life, a 'gang' of at least five individuals would try to rob him of the scooter and the mobile phone.<br> The 16-year-old reaction would follow the knives that reached him to his head and back. Research is underway by the authors of the attack, who fled before the arrival of the flyers.&nbsp;
